{
  "stem": "2966.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they were count-- we had to stand on attention as long till their count was right.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But that evening, they took just a few people out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I was one of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't remember why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "A friend of mine that lives in this building, Igor [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Klink ?], was with me, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He was also as lucky [? as me. ?] We were taken to dig out mass graves, take the people out that were buried for about three years already, put them on the-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we used to put them on-- on wood that the whole camp had to gather together.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They used to-- after work, they used to march the whole camp, which may be 20,000 people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And everybody had to bring a piece of wood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Where they got it from, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we used to dig out the people, put it on a stretcher, walk out from the mass grave, where we saw-- the grave was dug out in a [INAUDIBLE], where the people were preserved to such a degree.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They were all naked, but if there was a piece of cloth somewhere, you could see the colors of it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You could see mothers with their children in their arms.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We had to walk up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "An SS man was standing there with a pair of pliers and used to examine every head.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And where there ever was any gold, he used to pull it out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we threw those dead bodies on a-- on a mass point.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And after a while, they used to pour gasoline on it and burn it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "After they burned it, we used to take the bones and had big rollers, like your roll the street with, the asphalt.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
